features: Versatile USB-C Hub: This USB-C hub offers a comprehensive set of seven functions, including 4K HDMI video output, 100W Power Delivery, USB-C port, two USB-A 5 Gbps data ports, and microSD and SD card readers. It provides a wide range of connectivity and expansion options for your computer.

4K HDMI Video Output: With support for 4K resolution HDMI video output, you can connect to high-definition monitors, TVs, or projectors, delivering crisp images and video for various entertainment and work needs.

100W Power Delivery: Featuring 100 watts of power delivery capability, it can rapidly charge connected devices, including MacBook Air, MacBook Pro, and other compatible devices, making the charging process more efficient.

Multiple USB Ports: In addition to the USB-C port, there are two USB-A 5 Gbps data ports, enabling you to connect various USB devices like external hard drives, keyboards, mice, and more, facilitating high-speed data transfer.

Built-in Card Reader: The hub also includes microSD and SD card readers, allowing you to easily access and transfer data from memory cards. This feature is particularly useful for photographers and other professionals who need to read storage cards, eliminating the need for additional card readers. This hub is suitable for MacBook Air, MacBook Pro, XPS, and other devices, providing them with enhanced connectivity and expansion capabilities.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Primary hub for my M2 macbook
reviews.reviewText: Got this to use with an M2 macbook that I travel often with and, despite traveling, often end up needing all the extra ports including network + displays. No issues with this one. Pass-thru PD works great. HDMI has not yet driven a 4k display but does work well on a 1080p ultrawide, so I'm satisfied with that. If anything I wish it had MORE ports - USB-A specifically - but I'm using an extra USB hub on one of them without issue (I need to plug in: fingerprint reader, security key, headset, mouse/keyboard receiver, USB data sticks, etc on the reg). Overall, quite pleased! Have only had a chance to use the microSD reader, not the full SD reader, but that's a nice-to-have when reviewing security or dashboard camera footage (rare, but hey, extra features so I can't complain.Overall quite happy with this. I wish a bigger version existed with more ports, but this is a solid option for a traveling technician's kit.
